<ansi fg="yellow-bold">target</ansi> - Set or show combat target

<ansi fg="cyan">Usage:</ansi>
  target          - Show current target
  target <name>   - Set a new target

<ansi fg="cyan">Description:</ansi>
  In twitch combat, allows you to set a persistent combat target.
  Once set, you can use the attack command without specifying a
  target to continue attacking the same opponent.

<ansi fg="cyan">Examples:</ansi>
  target          - Show who you're currently targeting
  target rat      - Set your target to a rat
  target guard    - Set your target to a guard

<ansi fg="cyan">Note:</ansi>
  This command is only available when twitch combat is active.
  Your target is automatically cleared when you leave the room.

<ansi fg="yellow">See Also:</ansi> attack, cleartarget, balance